==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|slimig|slīmiġ|slimy|lang=ang}}, equivalent to {{suffix|slime|y}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|slijmig|lang=nl}}, {{term|slijmerig||slimy|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|schleimig||slimy|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|slemmig||slimy|lang=sv}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈslaɪ.mi/}}
*: {{rhymes|aɪmi}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|slimier|slimiest}}

# Of or pertaining to, resembling, of the nature of, covered or daubed with, yielding, abounding in [[slime]]; [[viscous]]; [[glutinous]].
#: '''''Slimy''' things did crawl with legs ''
#: ''Upon the slimy sea. &mdash;Coleridge.''
# {{slang|figuratively}} friendly in a false, [[calculating]] way; [[underhanded]]; [[sneaky]].

====Synonyms====
* (slippery) [[lubricous]]
* (underhanded) [[conniving]]

